<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-1252] Segfault in Ruby deserializer</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-1252</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There is a segfault bug in the native Ruby deserializer that was introduced with &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-1189&quot; title=&quot;Ruby deserializer speed improvements&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;THRIFT-1189&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;THRIFT-1189&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. The @index variable of MemoryBufferTransport is not always correctly updated from native code when GARBAGE_BUFFER_SIZE is exceeded.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Will attach the patch shortly.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Thrift 0.7.0dev (revision 1152979)&lt;br/&gt;
Ruby 1.9.2&lt;br/&gt;
OS X 10.6, Linux x86_64&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
